The paper discusses the use of crowdsourcing for machine learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on improving the quality of crowdsourced labels through the use of approval voting and incentive mechanisms suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect to the research. The use of optimization techniques and theoretical guarantees of optimality suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.CY). Finally, the empirical studies conducted on Amazon Mechanical Turk suggest a focus on social and information networks (cs.SI) as well.
